  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2017-05-23T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Community Reentry Act of 2017\n\nThis bill amends the federal criminal code to modify requirements with respect to the pre-release placement of inmates in residential reentry centers. Specifically, it adds a requirement for the Bureau of Prisons to place a prisoner in a residential reentry center that is within 50 miles of the prisoner's permanent legal address, subject to bed space availability."
  }, 
